[1
Date: Wed 17 Jan 2001 13:58:04 -0300
From: Dr. Lloyd Validum <validuml@guyana.net.gy>

Dengue Fever Infection of Travellers to Guyana-Brazil Border
------------------------------------------------------------
[A total of 3 persons returning to Georgetown from a recent visit to the
border town of Lethem on the Brazil-Guyana Border tested IgM-positive for
Dengue virus. [When seen at my clinic they also have florid symptoms of
classical dengue fever.
There are reports of more similar cases in Lethem on the border with
Brazil. Malaria was been ruled out in those cases as [blood smears were
reported
negative. Samples have been sent on to the Ministry of Health of Guyana
for confirmatory dengue testing and possible virus [serotype identification.
[The affected individuals had traveled to Lethem between the end of Dec
2000 and the first week of Jan 2001; symptoms of dengue fever [became
apparent late last week and during this week. As far as I am aware, the
Ministry is in the process of taking action.
I would like to know if anyone on the Brazilian side of the border [i.e. in
Bom Fin or Boa Vista could say if there have been any recent cases of
dengue fever in Roraima State, and if so [has the serotype(s) been
established?
--
Dr. Lloyd Validum
Tropimed
33 Alexander Street
Kitty, Georgetown
Guyana
<validuml@guyana.net.gy>
